# Parse / Sashido data access

## Client-side reads

```tsx
import { useFindData, useFindDataSecure } from "@repo/provider";

const { data, refetch } = useFindData({
  objectName: "Record",
  fields: ["objectId", "name"],
  projectId,
});
```

Use `useFindDataSecure` when the query requires master key (runs via edge function).

## Client-side writes

```tsx
import useDataHandlerSecure from "@repo/provider/general/data/useDataHandlerSecure";

const { createData, updateData, deleteData } = useDataHandlerSecure();
```

All operations go through `app/api/data/route.ts` — never call Sashido REST directly from components.

## API route pattern

Both apps have identical edge routes at `app/api/data/route.ts`:
- Headers: `X-Parse-Application-Id`, `X-Parse-REST-API-Key`, optional `X-Parse-Session-Token`, optional `X-Parse-Master-Key`
- Session from cookie (`SESSION_TOKEN` env)

## Rules

- Never import or use `SASHIDO_MASTER_KEY` in client components
- Never add master-key headers in browser-side fetch/axios
- Add `projectId` pointer when creating project-scoped records
- Reference: `packages/provider/src/general/data/README_SECURE_DATA_HANDLER.md`
